{"id": "posture-paused-refuses", "tags": ["posture", "refusal"], "input": {"case": "posture_refusal", "posture": "C_paused"}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.refused", "value": true}, {"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.reason", "value": "posture"}], "notes": "C_paused is a hard stop regardless of firm-role-gates flag. Exercises posture_gate._evaluate_posture, not adapter logic."}
{"id": "posture-cleared-allows", "tags": ["posture", "negative"], "input": {"case": "posture_refusal", "posture": "A_cleared"}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.refused", "value": false}, {"type": "key_present", "path": "output.reason"}], "notes": "Negative case: cleared matters pass the gate for any authenticated actor; reason key present but null."}
{"id": "posture-unknown-fails-closed", "tags": ["posture", "refusal", "negative"], "input": {"case": "posture_refusal", "posture": "Z_bogus"}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.refused", "value": true}, {"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.reason", "value": "unknown_posture"}], "notes": "A posture string outside the canonical vocabulary must deny (fail closed), per the defensive branch in _evaluate_posture."}
{"id": "posture-live-khan-matter", "tags": ["posture", "live-db"], "input": {"case": "posture_refusal", "matter_slug": "khan-v-acme-trading-2026"}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.posture", "value": "B_mixed"}, {"type": "key_present", "path": "output.refused"}], "notes": "Reads the live posture off the seeded Khan matter (default B_mixed). refused depends on LEGALISE_FIRM_ROLE_GATES_ENABLED (dormant=false locally), so only shape + posture are asserted."}
{"id": "summary-named-doc-match", "tags": ["deterministic-summary"], "input": {"case": "deterministic_summary", "user_content": "summarise the witness statement", "documents": [{"filename": "contract_acme_2026.pdf", "tag": "contract", "text": "Agreement between..."}, {"filename": "witness_statement_khan.docx", "text": "I, Mr Khan..."}]}, "judges": [{"type": "not_null", "path": "output.matched_document"}, {"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.matched_document", "value": "witness_statement_khan.docx"}], "notes": "PR #176 regression guard: named-document requests must match by filename/tag token overlap, not default to the first snippet."}
{"id": "summary-ambiguous-returns-null", "tags": ["deterministic-summary", "negative"], "input": {"case": "deterministic_summary", "user_content": "summarise the contract", "documents": [{"filename": "contract_v1.pdf", "text": "v1 text"}, {"filename": "contract_v2.pdf", "text": "v2 text"}]}, "judges": [{"type": "key_present", "path": "output.matched_document"}, {"type": "schema_valid", "schema": {"type": "object", "required": ["matched_document"], "properties": {"matched_document": {"type": "null"}}}}], "notes": "Tied scores are ambiguous — the matcher must return null and let the model path disambiguate, never guess."}
{"id": "summary-single-doc-shortcut", "tags": ["deterministic-summary"], "input": {"case": "deterministic_summary", "user_content": "summarise it", "documents": [{"filename": "grievance_letter.pdf", "text": "Dear Sir..."}]}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.matched_document", "value": "grievance_letter.pdf"}], "notes": "Single-document matter: the matcher short-circuits to the only candidate."}
{"id": "chain-intact-all-scopes", "tags": ["audit-chain", "live-db"], "input": {"case": "chain_intact"}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.verified", "value": true}, {"type": "length_bounds", "path": "output.issues", "max": 0}], "notes": "verify_audit_chain over every scope (all matters + system). Any hash drift, gap, or count mismatch between audit_entries and audit_chain fails this record."}
{"id": "grounding-khan-retrieves-real-sources", "tags": ["grounding", "retrieval", "live-db"], "input": {"case": "retrieval_grounding", "matter_slug": "khan-v-acme-trading-2026", "query": "why was Khan dismissed"}, "judges": [{"type": "length_bounds", "path": "output.sources", "min": 1}, {"type": "length_bounds", "path": "output.document_ids", "min": 1}, {"type": "not_null", "path": "output.document_ids.0"}, {"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.well_formed", "value": true}, {"type": "schema_valid", "path": "output.sources.0", "schema": {"type": "object", "required": ["document_id", "char_start", "char_end", "score"], "properties": {"document_id": {"type": "string", "minLength": 1}, "char_start": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0}, "char_end": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}, "score": {"type": "number"}}}}], "notes": "Grounding/citation eval: a real question over the seeded Khan matter runs the production hybrid retrieval (search_documents) and must return anchorable passages from real documents. Proves 'what did the AI see' is real, not the old 3-recent-docs stub. well_formed asserts every hit has a positive char span + score (citation integrity)."}
{"id": "grounding-empty-query-no-fabrication", "tags": ["grounding", "retrieval", "negative", "live-db"], "input": {"case": "retrieval_grounding", "matter_slug": "khan-v-acme-trading-2026", "query": ""}, "judges": [{"type": "key_equals", "path": "output.source_count", "value": 0}, {"type": "length_bounds", "path": "output.sources", "max": 0}], "notes": "Negative: an empty query must retrieve nothing, never fabricate sources. search_documents short-circuits on a blank query."}
